The paper discusses two different approaches for solving Petri games, which are a type of game model for distributed systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of binary decision diagrams (BDDs), which are commonly used in the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also deals with the synthesis of distributed systems, which could fall under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) or Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the use of quantified Boolean formulas (QBFs), which are commonly used in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
